1. Design a standardized response structure with the following components:
   - Core results (success/failure, data)
   - Context object (suggestions, risks, related tools, team activity, best practices)
   - Metadata (operation type, timestamp, affected files, session context)

2. Create utility functions to generate these enhanced responses

```javascript
// src/utils/responses.js

/**
 * Generate an enhanced MCP response with context and metadata
 * @param {Object} result - The core operation result
 * @param {Object} context - Contextual information
 * @param {Object} metadata - Operation metadata
 * @returns {Object} Enhanced response object
 */
function createEnhancedResponse(result, context = {}, metadata = {}) {
  return {
    result: {
      success: result.success || false,
      data: result.data || null,
      message: result.message || ''
    },
    context: {
      suggestions: context.suggestions || [],
      risks: context.risks || [],
      relatedTools: context.relatedTools || [],
      teamActivity: context.teamActivity || [],
      bestPractices: context.bestPractices || []
    },
    metadata: {
      operationType: metadata.operationType || 'unknown',
      timestamp: metadata.timestamp || new Date().toISOString(),
      affectedFiles: metadata.affectedFiles || [],
      sessionContext: metadata.sessionContext || {}
    }
  };
}

module.exports = { createEnhancedResponse };
```

